context","creat","custom","data","demo","detail","differ","each","entri","example:","experi","fast","features:","feed","field","file","global","global!","great","group","introduct","layout","layouts,","lightn","like:","log","look","master","migrat","mobil","new","object","object.","offer","opportun","opportunity.","page","particular","place","popul","power","pre","predefin","process","profiles.","publish","put","quick","record","record.","records,","records.","relat","relationship","salesforc","screen","share","shortcut","specif","speed","supported:","thing","three","type","uniqu","up","updat","user","valu","way"],"pipeline":["stopWordFilter","stemmer"]},"store":{"./":{"url":"./","title":"Introduction","keywords":"","body":"Mastering Salesforce Lightning Experience\n"},"chap-1/body.html":{"url":"chap-1/body.html","title":"Lightning Architecture","keywords":"","body":"Lightning Architecture\n"},"chap-2/body.html":{"url":"chap-2/body.html","title":"Classic Architecture","keywords":"","body":"Classic Architecture\n"},"chap-11/body.html":{"url":"chap-11/body.html","title":"Migration to Lightning","keywords":"","body":"Migration to Lightning\n"},"chap-11/actions.html":{"url":"chap-11/actions.html","title":"Actions","keywords":"","body":"Actions\nWhat are Actions?\nActions offer a fast way to do things like:\n\ncreating records\nlogging calls\nsharing files\n\nActions are three powerful features:\n\nshortcut\npage layout - each action comes with its own unique layout that you can customize\npredefined fields - A great way to speed up the process of data entry is to pre-populate values for certain fields on an action layout\n\nQuick actions in Salesforce Mobile  at the bottom of the screen\n\nTypes of Actions\n\nGlobal Actions\nObject Specific Actions\n\nGlobal Actions\nGlobal actions let users create records, but the new record has no relationship with other records.\nGlobal actions can’t update a record.\nGlobal Actions can be put anywhere actions are supported:\n\non record detail pages\nthe feed or Chatter groups\n\nGlobal Publisher Layouts\nThe global layout only applies to the action bar in places like:\n\nFeed\nChatter groups\nonly on pages that aren’t related to a specific object since it is GLOBAL!\nAfter creating global publisher layouts, you can assign them to different user profiles.\n\n\nDemo\n\nObject-specific Actions\nObject-specific actions let users create or update records in the context of a particular object.\nExample: an action associated with the opportunity object is only available when a user is looking at an opportunity.\nGlobal Actions can be put anywhere actions are supported:\n\non record detail pages\nthe feed or Chatter groups\n\n"}}}